CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G1/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe government's wide-ranging media
OL,7,Fgreen paper, Watch this Space, puts the
OL,8,Ffuture of the terrestrial TV aerial up
OL,9,Ffor debate, proposes forcing social
OL,10,Fmedia to surface trustworthy news, and
OL,11,Fopens the door to a wholly reformed
OL,12,Fpublic service broadcasting system.
OL,14,FPublished today by the Department for
OL,15,FCulture, Media and Sport, Watch this
OL,16,FSpace: a New Strategic Direction for UK
OL,17,FMedia opens a public consultation built
OL,18,Faround three goals:
OL,20,F- fostering a healthy information
OL,21,Fenvironment where trustworthy news is
OL,22,Feasy to find;
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14902
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,F- ensuring audiences keep universal
OL,7,Faccess to high-quality television;
OL,9,F- and supporting the public service
OL,10,Fmedia (PSM) providers at the centre of
OL,11,Fthe domestic industry.
OL,13,FIn his foreword, Ian Murray, Minister
OL,14,Ffor Creative Industries, Media and
OL,15,FArts, recalls evenings spent around the
OL,16,Ffamily television set and warns that
OL,17,Fthe benefits of that shared culture are
OL,18,Funder pressure in an age where "a
OL,19,Flimited selection of broadcast channels
OL,20,Fhas given way to an explosion of
OL,21,Fseemingly unlimited content, accessed
OL,22,Fprimarily via the internet".
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14903
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe strategy, he writes, is not
OL,7,Fdesigned to stop change but to put
OL,8,Ftechnology "in our service, not us in
OL,9,Fits".
OL,11,FThe paper is explicitly intended to be
OL,12,Fread alongside the separate BBC Charter
OL,13,FReview green paper, Britain's Story:
OL,14,Fthe Next Chapter, whose own
OL,15,Fconsultation closed in March 2026.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14904
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,GTHE END OF THE AERIAL ERA
OL,8,FThe most consequential proposal
OL,9,Fconcerns the future of digital
OL,10,Fterrestrial television (DTT) ` the
OL,11,Faerial-delivered signal that underpins
OL,12,FFreeview, and still the only way of
OL,13,Fwatching TV in just over four million
OL,14,FUK households.
OL,16,FThe government reaffirms its commitment
OL,17,Fto keeping DTT running until at least
OL,18,F31st December 2034, but says no
OL,19,Fdecision has been taken on what happens
OL,20,Fafter that and that a managed
OL,21,Fswitch-off is, in its view, inevitable.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14905
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FIt is consulting on two options.
OL,8,FOption 1 would deliver an industry-led
OL,9,Ftransition to internet protocol
OL,10,Ftelevision (IPTV) by 2034, with no
OL,11,Fextension of the platform beyond that
OL,12,Fpoint and the freeing-up of DTT
OL,13,Fspectrum from 2035.
OL,15,FOption 2 would grant a ten-year
OL,16,Fextension to 2044, during which the
OL,17,Fplatform would shrink from six
OL,18,Fmultiplexes to three, cutting the
OL,19,Fcarriage costs broadcasters pay while
OL,20,Fpreserving overall reach.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14906
SC,0006
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FA third "do nothing" baseline, letting
OL,7,Fthe market decide, is described but
OL,8,Fexplicitly ruled out as too disorderly
OL,9,Fand damaging to viewers.
OL,11,FThe government states it believes there
OL,12,Fis a "compelling case" for the earlier
OL,13,F2034 date, while stressing that the
OL,14,Fmove must be handled so that "no one is
OL,15,Fleft behind" and is consulting on 2044
OL,16,Fto gather a range of views.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14907
SC,0007
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G7/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FNotably, the paper warns that "no
OL,7,Fassumption should be made at this stage
OL,8,Fthat public funding will be available
OL,9,Fto support a transition", placing the
OL,10,Fonus on industry to propose and fund
OL,11,Fsolutions.
OL,13,FThe case for change is financial.
OL,15,FWhile DTT remains vital for the 4.01
OL,16,Fmillion broadcast-only homes recorded
OL,17,Fin 2024 (alongside 16.61 million hybrid
OL,18,Fhouseholds), the largely fixed cost of
OL,19,Frunning the network is becoming
OL,20,Funsustainable as viewing migrates
OL,21,Fonline.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14908
SC,0008
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G8/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe paper forecasts IPTV-only homes
OL,7,Frising from around seven million in
OL,8,F2024 to nearly 21 million by 2034, with
OL,9,Fbroadcast-only homes falling to about
OL,10,F1.51 million by 2034 and roughly half a
OL,11,Fmillion by 2044.
OL,13,FThe accompanying cost-benefit analysis
OL,14,Foffers an early, deliberately
OL,15,Fprovisional comparison.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14909
SC,0009
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G9/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FIt puts the net present value of the
OL,7,F2034 option at about #1.37 billion and
OL,8,Fthe 2044 option at about #1.67 billion,
OL,9,Fwith most of the monetised benefit on
OL,10,Fboth paths coming from releasing the
OL,11,F500MHz and 600MHz spectrum bands for
OL,12,Fmobile use.
OL,14,FBecause of overlapping ranges and
OL,15,Fsignificant unmonetised factors, the
OL,16,Fanalysis pointedly makes no
OL,17,Frecommendation between the two.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14910
SC,0010
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G10/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe government promises a support
OL,7,Fpackage modelled partly on the 2008 to
OL,8,F2012 digital switchover, targeted at
OL,9,Folder, rural, disabled and lower-income
OL,10,Fviewers, and says a transition plan and
OL,11,Ffinal decision will follow in a white
OL,12,Fpaper later this year.
OL,14,FIt also flags knock-on risks to radio,
OL,15,Fdrawing on the separate Radio Review
OL,16,Flaunched in February 2026, and to
OL,17,Fbroadcasting infrastructure that forms
OL,18,Fpart of the UK's critical national
OL,19,Finfrastructure.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14911
SC,0011
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G11/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,GFORCING PLATFORMS TO SURFACE TRUSTED
OL,7,GNEWS
OL,9,FThe paper frames the shift of news
OL,10,Fconsumption online as "a turning point
OL,11,Ffor our democracy".
OL,13,FMore than half of UK adults now get
OL,14,Fnews via social media, rising to 75 per
OL,15,Fcent of 16 to 24-year-olds, overall
OL,16,Ftrust in UK news has fallen seven
OL,17,Fpoints since 2018 to 35 per cent, and
OL,18,Fonly 45 per cent of adults feel
OL,19,Fconfident judging whether a source is
OL,20,Ftruthful.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14912
SC,0012
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G12/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FTo counter the spread of misinformation
OL,7,Fand deepfakes, the government will
OL,8,Fexplore legislation to create a
OL,9,Fprominence regime specifically for
OL,10,Ftrustworthy news on social media, and
OL,11,Fpotentially on video-sharing platforms,
OL,12,Frequiring them to make such news
OL,13,Fdiscoverable within their interfaces.
OL,15,FThe regime could extend beyond PSM
OL,16,Fproviders to national and local news
OL,17,Fpublishers.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14913
SC,0013
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G13/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe paper cites the disorder that
OL,7,Ffollowed the 2024 Southport stabbings,
OL,8,Fwhen Ofcom identified algorithmic
OL,9,Famplification of false claims as
OL,10,Fcontributing directly to real-world
OL,11,Fviolence, as evidence of why reliable
OL,12,Fnews matters most in a crisis, and
OL,13,Fnotes that local media helped
OL,14,Fde-escalate tensions at the same time.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14914
SC,0014
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G14/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FA central difficulty the paper concedes
OL,7,Fis defining a "trustworthy news
OL,8,Fprovider". It has not settled on
OL,9,Fcriteria and floats the recognised news
OL,10,Fpublisher definition in the Online
OL,11,FSafety Act 2023 as a possible starting
OL,12,Fpoint, alongside principles that any
OL,13,Fregime be audience-led, future-proofed,
OL,14,Foutcomes-based and protective of media
OL,15,Fplurality and freedom.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14915
SC,0015
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G15/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,GMEDIA LITERACY AND FIGHT AGAINST
OL,7,GDEEPFAKES
OL,9,FTwo further measures accompany the news
OL,10,Fproposals.
OL,12,FThe government will explore a new
OL,13,Fstatutory duty on PSM providers to
OL,14,Fdevelop, deliver and report on media
OL,15,Fliteracy strategies, leveraging their
OL,16,Ftrust and reach (the BBC's news alone
OL,17,Freaches 67 per cent of UK adults).
OL,19,FAny such duty, it stresses, must be
OL,20,Fbalanced within a sustainable PSM
OL,21,Fcompact.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14916
SC,0016
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G16/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FSeparately, it will explore a new joint
OL,7,Finitiative to coordinate the UK's
OL,8,Ffragmented media literacy sector, which
OL,9,Fa 2025 House of Lords inquiry found to
OL,10,Fbe working in silos.
OL,12,FOn artificial intelligence, the paper
OL,13,Fsets out several strands:
OL,15,F- an AI Labelling Taskforce to
OL,16,Frecommend best practice for marking
OL,17,FAI-generated content, with an interim
OL,18,Freport due in the autumn;
OL,20,F- a consultation on digital replicas
OL,21,Fthis summer to address unauthorised use
OL,22,Fof a person's likeness;
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14917
SC,0017
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G17/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,F- and a world-first deepfake detection
OL,7,Fevaluation framework being developed
OL,8,Fwith partners including Microsoft.
OL,10,FIt cites BBC research finding that 51
OL,11,Fper cent of AI answers to news
OL,12,Fquestions had significant issues.
OL,14,FThe paper also references the under-16
OL,15,Fsocial media ban announced on 15th
OL,16,FJune, with further detail on measures
OL,17,Fsuch as overnight curfews promised in
OL,18,FJuly.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14918
SC,0018
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G18/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,GREWRITING THE RULES FOR THE DIGITAL
OL,7,GERA
OL,9,FThe green paper argues that a
OL,10,Fregulatory framework designed for
OL,11,Fanalogue broadcasting can no longer
OL,12,Fcope with a world in which 85 per cent
OL,13,Fof adults use a video-on-demand service
OL,14,Feach month, YouTube accounts for a
OL,15,Fgrowing share of TV-set viewing, and
OL,16,Funregulated manufacturer channels mimic
OL,17,Ftraditional TV guides.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14919
SC,0019
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G19/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FIt records recent steps already taken:
OL,7,Ffrom 1st April 2026, mainstream
OL,8,Fvideo-on-demand services with more than
OL,9,F500,000 users (such as Netflix, Disney+
OL,10,Fand ITVX) were designated for enhanced
OL,11,F"Tier 1" regulation under the Media Act
OL,12,F2024, and more electronic programme
OL,13,Fguides, including Sky Glass and Freely,
OL,14,Fwere brought under Ofcom's remit.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14920
SC,0020
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F149A1784142692
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}        G20/30
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWS+CGovernment green paper outlines
OL,4,CFreeview switch-off options
OL,5,
OL,6,FLooking further ahead, the government
OL,7,Fwill open a period of stakeholder
OL,8,Fengagement on more fundamental reform,
OL,9,Fwith a stated long-term goal of
OL,10,Fshifting away from regulating by how
OL,11,Fcontent is delivered towards regulating
OL,12,Fby where audiences find and consume
OL,13,FTV-like content, ensuring consistent
OL,14,Fstandards regardless of platform.
OL,16,FIt restates its pledge to cut the
OL,17,Fadministrative cost of regulation on
OL,18,Fbusiness by a quarter, framing reform
OL,19,Fas both raising protections for viewers
OL,20,Fand lifting outdated burdens off
OL,21,Fbroadcasters.
OL,23,EPub: 23-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,150,140,200,120,0,100
